have him drop in on you after lunch.

75
00:04:32,440 --> 00:04:35,079
That's okay. I figured I should
just stay home and rest...

76
00:04:35,240 --> 00:04:39,233
...in case, you know,
it's West Nile or something.

77
00:04:39,400 --> 00:04:43,518
All right. I'll be in my office all day if you
need me. I'll call in and check up on you.

78
00:04:44,080 --> 00:04:46,753
I may not pick up, you know.
I'll just be sleeping.

79
00:04:57,360 --> 00:04:59,510
-Hello?
-So, what are we doing today?

80
00:05:00,600 --> 00:05:03,194
-I'm sleeping.
-No, you're not.

81
00:05:03,360 --> 00:05:06,158
We're going to breakfast,
and then we're going shopping.

82
00:05:06,320 --> 00:05:07,594
Don't you have school?

83
00:05:07,760 --> 00:05:10,957
Yeah, but my mom's in Europe,
and my stepdad's completely clueless.

84
00:05:11,360 --> 00:05:14,432
Aren't you sick of me yet?
We've hung out every day this week.

85
00:05:14,680 --> 00:05:16,113
No. Why? Are you sick of me?

86
00:05:16,680 --> 00:05:19,911
No, no, of course not. It's just...

87
00:05:21,320 --> 00:05:22,639
...Jody's still here.

88
00:05:23,280 --> 00:05:26,477
-I thought she was going back to L.A.
-Yeah, yeah, she was, she was...

89
00:05:26,640 --> 00:05:31,111
...but we got into this huge fight,
and then....

90
00:05:31,280 --> 00:05:34,078
And then you spent the rest of the night
making up?

91
00:05:34,240 --> 00:05:36,310
Who's knocking on my door
at 9 in the morning?

92
00:05:36,480 --> 00:05:37,959
Yeah, right. Saved by the bell.

93
00:05:38,120 --> 00:05:40,634
Are you calling me
from outside my door?

94
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:43,234
Because that would be...

95
00:05:43,400 --> 00:05:45,038
...creepy.

96
00:05:45,200 --> 00:05:47,191
-Good to see you too, Alex.
-Seth.

97
00:05:47,400 --> 00:05:49,550
-Seth?
-Can I call you back?

98
00:05:49,880 --> 00:05:53,873
-Doesn't anyone go to school anymore?
-Listen, I'm sorry to wake you. I--

99
00:05:54,760 --> 00:05:57,035
-Do I hear water running?
-Yes.

100
00:05:57,600 --> 00:05:59,318
Jody's taking a shower.

101
00:05:59,480 --> 00:06:01,835
Jody. Jody's still here.

102
00:06:02,480 --> 00:06:06,189
That's great. That's fantastic. At least
you're not taking a shower together.

103
00:06:06,720 --> 00:06:09,314
-Look--
-I just need to know where I stand.

104
00:06:09,480 --> 00:06:12,472
Seth, I told you. I just--
I don't do relationships.

105
00:06:12,640 --> 00:06:14,517
Yeah, well, you did Jody. So to speak.

106
00:06:14,680 --> 00:06:16,511
Yes, and look how well that turned out.

107
00:06:16,680 --> 00:06:18,557
What is that supposed to mean?

108
00:06:18,720 --> 00:06:21,075
-Jody.
-Seth.

109
00:06:22,080 --> 00:06:25,470
Sorry. I would have introduced you guys,
but I didn't want you to meet.

110
00:06:26,160 --> 00:06:30,039
I'm going back to bed.
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

111
00:06:33,480 --> 00:06:36,517
You maybe wanna grab breakfast?
We could go down to the....

112
00:06:37,480 --> 00:06:42,395
--which you see in the center
of the diagram here and multi-angle here.

113
00:06:42,560 --> 00:06:45,074
Okay? All right, see you next time.

114
00:06:45,240 --> 00:06:48,471
So are Kirsten and Sandy gonna care
that Seth skipped first period?

115
00:06:48,640 --> 00:06:50,949
They won't be excited,
but they're easygoing.

116
00:06:51,120 --> 00:06:52,439
Really? Kirsten is?

117
00:06:52,600 --> 00:06:54,238
Sandy is. Kirsten's more....

118
00:06:54,400 --> 00:06:57,472
-Like her dad.
-ln some ways, I guess.

119
00:06:57,960 --> 00:06:59,359
Am l?

120
00:06:59,640 --> 00:07:01,710
I mean, he's my dad too, so....

121
