145
00:08:25,280 --> 00:08:28,431
-Sandy. You're moving in?
-I'll take it.

146
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:30,477
So, what are you doing in town?

147
00:08:30,920 --> 00:08:34,037
Really? Everything okay?

148
00:08:36,400 --> 00:08:39,710
I understand.
We can talk about it when you get here.

149
00:08:51,600 --> 00:08:53,192
What's up with Cohen?

150
00:08:53,360 --> 00:08:54,998
I guess it didn't go well with Alex.

151
00:08:55,160 --> 00:08:57,310
-She broke up with him?
-I don't know. Maybe.

152
00:08:57,480 --> 00:09:00,916
Well, why don't you go find out.
And then report back to me.

153
00:09:05,960 --> 00:09:07,996
So how'd it go?

154
00:09:09,400 --> 00:09:12,949
The good news is, she told Jody
to get the hell out too, so....

155
00:09:13,760 --> 00:09:15,239
I'm sorry, man.

156
00:09:15,400 --> 00:09:17,630
-Thanks. It's all right.
-Now you can get back...

157
00:09:17,800 --> 00:09:20,360
-...to your life, right?
-I don't have a life, remember?

158
00:09:20,520 --> 00:09:22,795
Then you should get one.
Do something for you.

159
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:24,718
-Go sailing.
-All right.

160
00:09:24,880 --> 00:09:27,633
-Continue to doodle.
-Okay.

161
00:09:29,720 --> 00:09:32,712
-This is what you should be doing.
-What?

162
00:09:32,880 --> 00:09:36,111
Drawing the women who wronged me
as whip-wielding warrior princesses?

163
00:09:36,280 --> 00:09:38,236
-Yeah, in your own comic.
-Yeah, okay.

164
00:09:38,400 --> 00:09:40,231
-Dude, you're awesome.
-I appreciate it.

165
00:09:40,400 --> 00:09:44,916
Hey, Cohen, I got you a double latte
because you looked sad.

166
00:09:45,080 --> 00:09:47,116
-Thanks.
-Cohen's gonna do his own comic.

167
00:09:47,280 --> 00:09:49,191
-He is?
-No, I don't-- Well, I don't know.

168
00:09:49,360 --> 00:09:51,920
What are you talking about?
Do you not wanna do it?

169
00:09:52,080 --> 00:09:55,072
-No, I do, sort of.
-Then let's bounce some ideas around.

170
00:09:55,240 --> 00:09:57,390
-Study hall, right now. Let's go.
-All right.

171
00:09:57,560 --> 00:10:00,711
-Thanks for the coffee, Summer.
-Yeah, thank you very much.

172
00:10:01,160 --> 00:10:02,434
You're welcome.

173
00:10:03,640 --> 00:10:06,154
So you and Seth are...?

174
00:10:06,320 --> 00:10:09,756
Friends. I hope. Someday.

175
00:10:10,400 --> 00:10:13,836
-And you and Jody are...?
-Over. Finished. For good.

176
00:10:15,160 --> 00:10:18,357
Really? How does she feel about that?

177
00:10:19,640 --> 00:10:23,838
She hates me now, but, I mean, we
mean too much to each other to let....

178
00:10:25,600 --> 00:10:28,637
That bitch. She stole my necklace.

179
00:10:28,800 --> 00:10:31,109
-Which one?
-We bought each other these matching...

180
00:10:31,280 --> 00:10:34,158
...heart-shaped necklaces,
like, a year ago, and mine's gone.

181
00:10:34,320 --> 00:10:35,833
I can't believe her.

182
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:38,912
-How do you know she took it?
-Because she was using the fact...

183
00:10:39,080 --> 00:10:43,312
...that I still wear mine as a sign that
I'm not over her, which I am. I just....

184
00:10:43,800 --> 00:10:45,119
I loved it.

185
00:10:45,720 --> 00:10:48,029
Well, so let's go get it.

186
00:10:48,200 --> 00:10:50,475
You wanna go to L.A.? Now?

187
00:10:51,040 --> 00:10:52,951
-I can't. I have work.
-We'll go tomorrow.

188
00:10:53,120 --> 00:10:54,951
-How? You have school.
-No.

189
00:10:55,120 --> 00:10:56,678
I have a mom who's spa-hopping...

190
00:10:56,840 --> 00:11:00,116
...and a stepdad who doesn't care
about anyone but himself.

191
00:11:00,680 --> 00:11:03,240
Come on.
You can't let her steal your heart.

192
00:11:07,160 --> 00:11:09,879
At the tone, leave a message
for Julie, Caleb or Marissa.

193
00:11:10,040 --> 00:11:12,429
We 'll get back to you
as soon as we can.

194
00:11:22,840 --> 00:11:25,957
-Kirsten's not here.
-l' m actually here to see you.

195
00:11:26,120 --> 00:11:27,633
-lf you have a second.
-I don't.

196
00:11:28,240 --> 00:11:29,958
It's about Lindsay.

197
00:11:32,320 --> 00:11:34,038
Shut the door.

198
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:40,560
-What about her?
-She's been asking questions about you.

199
00:11:40,720 --> 00:11:44,315
Who you are, what you're like. I told her.
She still wants to get to know you.

200
00:11:45,680 --> 00:11:47,159
