201
00:11:47,560 --> 00:11:50,199
She has no idea I'm here.
I just thought maybe I should--

202
00:11:50,360 --> 00:11:53,796
Continue to position yourself between
me and members of my family.

203
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:56,753
If I wanted a relationship with Lindsay,
I would have one.

204
00:11:56,920 --> 00:11:58,831
-Funny. That's what she said.
-Smart girl.

205
00:11:59,000 --> 00:12:00,513
You have no idea.

206
00:12:00,800 --> 00:12:02,358
You should, though.

207
00:12:03,840 --> 00:12:06,593
How's your relationship
with your father, Ryan?

208
00:12:06,760 --> 00:12:08,432
Is he still in jail?

209
00:12:09,160 --> 00:12:11,628
And you would be, too,
if it weren't for Sandy.

210
00:12:11,800 --> 00:12:15,634
So I guess Lindsay and I are both better
off. Thank you so much for your time.

211
00:12:34,280 --> 00:12:38,114
I was under the impression
that you'd become a successful lawyer.

212
00:12:38,680 --> 00:12:40,636
Oh, my God.

213
00:12:41,440 --> 00:12:42,998
How are you, Max?

214
00:12:44,360 --> 00:12:47,830
It's hard to believe it's been 20 years
since you were my favorite student.

215
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:53,358
It is so good to see you. Well,
come on in to my-- My new office.

216
00:12:53,640 --> 00:12:56,916
So, what have you been up to?

217
00:12:57,080 --> 00:13:00,789
Well, l-- Let's see, l-- I left Berkeley.

218
00:13:00,960 --> 00:13:02,552
I moved to Princeton.

219
00:13:02,720 --> 00:13:06,190
-I am retired now.
-Congratulations.

220
00:13:06,960 --> 00:13:08,234
So, what brings you here?

221
00:13:09,560 --> 00:13:11,551
Sandy, I need your help.

222
00:13:12,920 --> 00:13:14,751
I have to find Rebecca.

223
00:13:18,720 --> 00:13:21,473
Why now? After all this time?

224
00:13:25,640 --> 00:13:29,189
Well, Sandy, I've....
I've had a couple of strokes.

225
00:13:29,360 --> 00:13:31,271
The doctors told me...

226
00:13:31,440 --> 00:13:36,468
...that I should get my affairs in order
as soon as possible.

227
00:13:36,880 --> 00:13:40,919
I just wanna be able to see
my daughter once again before....

228
00:13:41,440 --> 00:13:42,839
I understand.

229
00:13:44,120 --> 00:13:47,715
Well, you know, I haven't heard a thing
since she ran away to Canada...

230
00:13:48,080 --> 00:13:49,559
...22 years ago.

231
00:13:49,720 --> 00:13:52,393
-You haven't heard from her?
-No, no, no. She and l...

232
00:13:52,560 --> 00:13:58,430
...weren't exactly on speaking terms,
even before the accident.

233
00:13:58,920 --> 00:14:03,391
I just thought that if she'd get in touch
with anybody, Sandy, it'd be you.

234
00:14:03,560 --> 00:14:05,357
You were the love of her life.

235
00:14:06,880 --> 00:14:08,996
That was a long time ago.

236
00:14:10,200 --> 00:14:12,031
-We were kids.
-No, she loved you, Sandy.

237
00:14:14,720 --> 00:14:16,836
Now, will you help me find her?

238
00:14:19,160 --> 00:14:21,230
I'll see what I can do.

239
00:14:23,120 --> 00:14:25,076
Thank you, Sandy.

240
00:14:25,480 --> 00:14:29,234
You know, I hate to stir up things when
you have a wife and a family and--

241
00:14:29,400 --> 00:14:31,994
No, my wife will understand.

242
00:14:32,160 --> 00:14:33,639
Will she?

243
00:14:39,520 --> 00:14:41,431
-You're going to prison?
-Just for the day.

244
00:14:41,600 --> 00:14:44,114
I have to drive to Lompoc
to see a prisoner there.

245
00:14:44,280 --> 00:14:46,077
-Who?
-An activist I knew...

246
00:14:46,240 --> 00:14:48,310
...back in my Berkeley days,
Joe Zukoski.

247
00:14:48,480 --> 00:14:49,754
I'll be back before dinner.

248
00:14:49,920 --> 00:14:53,310
-What do you have to talk to him about?
-Well, you know, a missing person.

249
00:14:53,480 --> 00:14:56,199
-Doing a favor for a friend.
-Your old law school professor.

250
00:14:56,360 --> 00:14:59,238
-Yeah.
-Who's missing?

251
00:15:00,600 --> 00:15:03,068
-Rebecca.
-As in Rebecca Bloom?

252
00:15:03,240 --> 00:15:05,629
-Love of your life?
-She is not the love of my life.

253
00:15:05,800 --> 00:15:09,156
-Sandy, you were engaged to be married.
-We were engaged to be engaged.

254
00:15:09,320 --> 00:15:11,550
Until she burned down a nuclear lab site.

255
00:15:11,720 --> 00:15:13,517
We don't know if she did that for sure.

256
00:15:13,680 --> 00:15:17,992
-Sandy, she fled the country.
-Well, I know, but her dad is dying...

257
00:15:18,160 --> 00:15:21,630
...and he asked me to find her for him.
He was my mentor in law school.

258
00:15:21,800 --> 00:15:23,995
I wouldn't be a lawyer
if it weren't for him.

259
00:15:24,160 --> 00:15:26,515
-I can't say no.
-What will you do when you find her?

260
00:15:26,680 --> 00:15:28,591
If I find her, I'll try convincing her...

261
00:15:28,760 --> 00:15:32,548
...to turn herself in and, you know,
let the case go to trial.

262
00:15:40,680 --> 00:15:43,035
Well, seems someone's
feeling better today.

263
00:15:43,200 --> 00:15:45,668
-Not really.
-Sorry to hear that.

264
00:15:47,800 --> 00:15:49,518
I called several times to check up...

265
00:15:49,680 --> 00:15:51,910
-...on you yesterday.
-I must have been asleep.

266
00:15:52,080 --> 00:15:53,832
Then I came home,
and you weren't here.

267
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:56,555
-I was worried.
-Gotta go.

268
00:15:56,720 --> 00:15:58,995
-Where?
-Out. To the doctor.

269
00:15:59,160 --> 00:16:01,799
-Marissa, come back here.
-Or what?

270
00:16:01,960 --> 00:16:04,997
You're not my dad. You know what?
If you want to parent someone...

271
00:16:05,160 --> 00:16:08,232
...why don't you go over
to Lindsay's house and ruin her life.

272
00:16:08,680 --> 00:16:10,830
That's right, you already have.

273
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:12,672
Don't wait up.

274
00:16:15,840 --> 00:16:17,478
So, what's it about?

275
00:16:19,320 --> 00:16:20,912
Heroes and, you know, villains.

276
00:16:21,240 --> 00:16:22,559
-Good and evil.
-Sure.

277
00:16:22,720 --> 00:16:24,312
Darkness, and then you have light.

278
00:16:24,480 --> 00:16:26,516
-You guys have no idea, do you?
-Not so much.

279
00:16:26,680 --> 00:16:29,877
But you have to admit, it's pretty
exciting. Our very own comic book.

280
00:16:30,040 --> 00:16:34,670
-Hey. It could be autobiographical.
-Yeah, it could.

281
00:16:34,840 --> 00:16:38,799
Yeah, the life of, like, a young Jewish
boy growing up in Orange County.

282
00:16:38,960 --> 00:16:41,918
-I like it very much already.
-A young Jewish boy with powers.

283
00:16:42,080 --> 00:16:43,513
Sure. A kid with a secret.

284
00:16:43,680 --> 00:16:46,319
-ln a town full of secrets.
-Fistfights, fashion shows.

285
00:16:46,480 --> 00:16:49,074
-Basically, life in Orange County.
-But with powers.

286
00:16:49,240 --> 00:16:50,958
I like it a lot, and--

287
00:16:52,240 --> 00:16:55,869
-What have you done to my boyfriend?
-Look, it was his idea in the first place.

288
00:16:56,040 --> 00:16:58,315
-We just had a major breakthrough.
-Y eah, we did.

289
00:16:58,480 --> 00:17:00,277
You realize how lame you just sounded?

290
00:17:00,560 --> 00:17:04,519
Now, now, Summer, if you're not nice,
somebody's not gonna be in the comic.

291
00:17:04,880 --> 00:17:07,519
Yeah. Shaking in my boots, Cohen.

292
00:17:09,720 --> 00:17:13,713
Sweetie.
I will see you out front after school.

293
00:17:16,480 --> 00:17:18,675
Actually, we're working after school.

294
00:17:19,120 --> 00:17:22,669
But I would love to, you know,
hang out with you a little bit later.

295
00:17:23,320 --> 00:17:25,276
Perhaps dinner and a movie?

296
00:17:26,520 --> 00:17:28,670
Well, I guess.
Just not a comic-book movie.

297
00:17:29,320 --> 00:17:31,072
-Comic-book movies suck anyways.
-True.

298
00:17:31,240 --> 00:17:34,232
-Dude, you didn't like X2? Really?
-I've seen better.

299
00:17:34,400 --> 00:17:36,868
What have you done to him?
I swear to God, Cohen...

300
00:17:37,040 --> 00:17:39,838
...if Brainstorming Boy
doesn't turn back into my boyfriend--

301
00:17:40,000 --> 00:17:43,310
-Brainstorming Boy. Brainstorming Lad.
-Brainstorm.

302
00:17:43,480 --> 00:17:45,630
Let's work with this. Brainstorming Kid.

303
00:17:45,800 --> 00:17:49,270
Brainstorming young ward
with a secret identity, which is...

304
00:17:49,440 --> 00:17:53,797
...at night he's Brainstorming Man,
and what that is, is he's a genius.

305
00:17:53,960 --> 00:17:57,430
The contracts have been vetted twice,
so I just need you to sign.

306
00:17:59,480 --> 00:18:01,198
Dad? Are you okay?

307
00:18:01,360 --> 00:18:03,555
Yeah, I'm fine. Sorry.

308
00:18:05,880 --> 00:18:08,189
You take good care of me.
Better than I deserve.

309
00:18:08,360 --> 00:18:10,828
-What's that mean?
-I haven't been the best father.

310
00:18:11,200 --> 00:18:12,952
Pretty much, no.

311
00:18:14,960 --> 00:18:17,952
-Are you still in touch with Lindsay?
-Y eah. Are you?

312
00:18:18,120 --> 00:18:22,511
-No. She doesn't ever bother calling me.
-Dad, she's in high school.

313
00:18:22,920 --> 00:18:27,436
If you wanna hear from Lindsay,
you have to call her.

314
00:18:30,160 --> 00:18:33,152
You were right.
Caleb Nichol is not a good guy.

315
00:18:33,320 --> 00:18:34,958
Why, what happened? Did he call you?

316
00:18:35,120 --> 00:18:37,111
No, but I A9-dot-com'd him
last night...

317
00:18:37,280 --> 00:18:40,590
...and, according to the OC Weekly,
he's everything that's wrong...

318
00:18:40,760 --> 00:18:43,911
...with Western civilization
all wrapped up in one guy...

319
00:18:44,080 --> 00:18:47,516
...so even if he did call me....

320
00:18:48,600 --> 00:18:51,239
Oh, my God. He's calling me.
It says the Newport Group.

321
00:18:51,400 --> 00:18:54,358
-Why is he calling me?
-No, it's not. It's probably Kirsten.

322
00:18:55,040 --> 00:18:58,191
Right. Sorry.

323
00:18:58,360 --> 00:19:01,796
-Hey, Kirsten.
-Lindsay. Caleb Nichol.

324
00:19:02,480 --> 00:19:04,710
I was thinking it's time
you and I sat down.

325
00:19:12,440 --> 00:19:14,192
What was that about?

326
00:19:14,960 --> 00:19:18,032
It was Caleb.
He wants to have dinner tonight.

327
00:19:18,200 --> 00:19:21,476
-You're kidding.
-Will you come with me?

328
00:19:21,640 --> 00:19:24,313
-I don't think that's a good idea.
-Please.

329
00:19:24,520 --> 00:19:26,636
I'm not gonna go without you.

330
00:19:27,680 --> 00:19:30,638
-He won't be happy about this.
-Do you care about his happiness?

331
00:19:30,800 --> 00:19:34,554
-I care about yours.
-Well, then I will see you tonight.

332
00:19:46,280 --> 00:19:48,589
So, what does the butterfly mean?

333
00:19:50,600 --> 00:19:53,319
It means I was drunk.

334
00:19:53,480 --> 00:19:54,754
No way.

335
00:19:54,920 --> 00:19:57,514
I was drunk. I had just been
emancipated from my parents.

336
00:19:57,680 --> 00:20:00,831
The words "Mom" and "Dad" with
an X through them was too expensive.

337
00:20:01,160 --> 00:20:03,151
You got emancipated?

338
00:20:03,320 --> 00:20:07,518
-I thought only child stars did that.
-Yep. Me, Hilary Duff, Lil' Bow Wow.

339
00:20:09,080 --> 00:20:10,354
Wait, so how did you do it?

340
00:20:10,760 --> 00:20:14,469
I petitioned the court. I had my parents
sign the form, which they were happy...

341
00:20:14,640 --> 00:20:18,155
...to do when they found out about
me and Jody, and that was it.

342
00:20:19,120 --> 00:20:20,473
I was free.

343
00:20:20,640 --> 00:20:22,596
Well, I wish I could do that.

344
00:20:22,880 --> 00:20:25,758
-Piss your parents off bad enough.
-Believe me, I've tried.

345
00:20:26,040 --> 00:20:28,315
Well, then I guess they really love you.

346
00:20:33,200 --> 00:20:34,872
Do you ever miss yours?

347
00:20:35,120 --> 00:20:36,394
Sometimes.

348
00:20:36,560 --> 00:20:39,028
But my friends are my family,
you know?

349
00:20:40,400 --> 00:20:41,674
I know.

350
00:20:48,960 --> 00:20:50,757
Let's open up A.

351
00:20:57,120 --> 00:20:59,111
Sandy Cohen.

352
00:20:59,720 --> 00:21:02,154
Couldn't believe it when they told me.

353
00:21:05,600 --> 00:21:06,953
How are you, Joe?

354
00:21:07,120 --> 00:21:10,999
Well, not as good as you.
You look good. Successful.

355
00:21:11,160 --> 00:21:13,276
What happened? You sell out?

356
00:21:13,720 --> 00:21:17,190
No, actually. I did 1 5 years
in the public defender's office.

357
00:21:17,560 --> 00:21:21,394
Good for you. Maybe you can work
me up an appeal and get me out of here.

358
00:21:21,560 --> 00:21:23,471
How? You confessed.

359
00:21:23,880 --> 00:21:27,555
To an act of civil disobedience,
not manslaughter.

360
00:21:27,720 --> 00:21:30,234
You set the place on fire,
and a man died.

361
00:21:30,400 --> 00:21:33,915
It was an accident. The custodian wasn't
supposed to be there. You know that.

362
00:21:37,440 --> 00:21:39,749
Like any of that matters now.

363
00:21:40,440 --> 00:21:41,759
What do you want, Sandy?

364
00:21:43,280 --> 00:21:44,713
I'm looking for Rebecca.

365
00:21:47,200 --> 00:21:50,078
Sandy Cohen has come to me
looking for Rebecca.

366
00:21:50,240 --> 00:21:51,798
Let it go.

367
00:21:51,960 --> 00:21:53,916
This isn't about you and me.

368
00:21:54,080 --> 00:21:57,516
When it comes to Rebecca,
it's always been about you and me.

369
00:21:57,760 --> 00:21:59,352
Well, not anymore.

370
00:22:00,840 --> 00:22:02,751
Okay.

371
00:22:03,640 --> 00:22:06,279
-Then what's this about?
-Her father.

372
00:22:07,320 --> 00:22:09,914
He's sick. He's looking for her.

373
00:22:11,440 --> 00:22:13,237
I'll tell you what.

374
00:22:13,840 --> 00:22:16,752
He can look as far and wide
as he wants to.

375
00:22:17,000 --> 00:22:19,116
He's never gonna find her.

376
00:22:19,320 --> 00:22:22,710
-So you're not gonna help me.
-I can't help you, Sandy.

377
00:22:23,200 --> 00:22:24,872
Rebecca...

378
00:22:25,720 --> 00:22:26,994
...she's dead.

379
00:22:36,440 --> 00:22:38,158
She's dead?

380
00:22:40,760 --> 00:22:42,113
I'm so sorry.

381
00:22:42,960 --> 00:22:45,190
I can't believe this.

382
00:22:46,160 --> 00:22:48,230
I can't believe it either.

383
00:22:49,080 --> 00:22:51,594
-Are you calling Max?
-No, an old friend of mine.

384
00:22:51,760 --> 00:22:54,911
A guy in the group. He's a lawyer
now in Vancouver. Hello, yes.

385
00:22:55,080 --> 00:22:58,277
-Directory assistance for Vancouver.
-Why? What will you find out?

386
00:22:58,440 --> 00:23:02,194
Y es, please, I'd like the number
for Mark Denham, D-E-N-H-A-M.

387
00:23:02,360 --> 00:23:03,634
Thank you.

388
00:23:04,240 --> 00:23:07,835
If she was sick, there'd be insurance
forms or hospital records or something.

389
00:23:08,000 --> 00:23:11,595
And, God forbid, if she were dead,
there'd be a death certificate.

390
00:23:14,480 --> 00:23:16,471
So you don't think she's dead.

391
00:23:17,240 --> 00:23:21,028
I can't believe that if she were dying,
she wouldn't try to contact her dad.

392
00:23:21,200 --> 00:23:22,474
Or you.

393
00:23:32,720 --> 00:23:35,234
We'll just get what we came for,
then get out of here.

394
00:23:35,400 --> 00:23:37,436
You all right? You seem nervous.

395
00:23:37,600 --> 00:23:39,238
No, I'm not. I just--

396
00:23:39,400 --> 00:23:42,949
Don't let her intimidate you, okay?
And let me do all the talking.

397
00:23:43,400 --> 00:23:47,678
And don't mention anything
about the necklace.

398
00:23:48,040 --> 00:23:49,712
-I thought you were over her.
-I am.

399
00:23:49,880 --> 00:23:53,236
I am. I just-- Don't let her
talk me into staying the night.

400
00:23:53,400 --> 00:23:55,436
You can't. You have to take me home.

401
00:23:55,600 --> 00:23:58,160
Right. Good one. Remember that.

402
00:24:05,720 --> 00:24:07,392
I had a feeling it might--

403
00:24:09,640 --> 00:24:11,517
What is she doing here?

404
00:24:14,320 --> 00:24:16,550
We came to get Alex's stuff.

405
00:24:18,960 --> 00:24:20,871
And we're not staying.

406
00:24:21,880 --> 00:24:23,677
If you say so.

407
00:24:32,040 --> 00:24:34,076
-Hey.
-Hey.

408
00:24:34,240 --> 00:24:38,552
Bryan Gatwood, a.k.a. Kid Chino,
the strong but silent youth...

409
00:24:38,720 --> 00:24:41,598
...from the wrong side of the tracks,
who, when provoked...

410
00:24:41,760 --> 00:24:44,069
...unleashes his fists of fury.

411
00:24:44,520 --> 00:24:47,353
Maybe we should change
his superhero name to Overdressed Lad.

412
00:24:47,520 --> 00:24:49,954
Lindsay asked me to be a buffer
between her and Caleb.

413
00:24:50,120 --> 00:24:52,270
I thought we'd work tonight.
Grandpa hates you.

414
00:24:52,440 --> 00:24:54,829
-I said that. She thinks I'm overreacting.
-Hey, man.

415
00:24:55,000 --> 00:24:58,788
At least you're on his radar. He once
asked my mom if I was mildly retarded.

416
00:24:58,960 --> 00:25:01,554
-Wait till he finds out about your powers.
-What powers?

417
00:25:01,720 --> 00:25:04,792
Turns out I don't make
a very convincing superhero.

418
00:25:05,680 --> 00:25:07,591
Well, you do have powers.

419
00:25:07,760 --> 00:25:10,433
-Hey, can I see these?
-Yeah, sure.

420
00:25:14,880 --> 00:25:17,713
-What are these?
-They're just sketches I did in Portland.

421
00:25:18,720 --> 00:25:21,359
-The summer without Summer.
-Has Zach seen these?

422
00:25:21,520 --> 00:25:24,034
-No, I'll show him tonight.
-No, you won't show Zach.

423
00:25:24,200 --> 00:25:26,589
-They're drawings.
-Of a girl you were obsessed with.

424
00:25:26,920 --> 00:25:30,230
First of all, "obsessed,"
it's a pretty strong word.

425
00:25:30,960 --> 00:25:33,190
Maybe you're right.
Therefore, I won't show him.

426
00:25:33,640 --> 00:25:35,790
-They're really good, though.
-Thanks.

427
00:25:35,960 --> 00:25:38,428
Hey. Don't let Grandpa
scare you, all right?

428
00:25:38,600 --> 00:25:41,478
Remember, you're Bryan Gatwood,
fists of fury.

429
00:25:54,680 --> 00:25:58,229
-Sure you don't want a beer?
-We have to drive back. T onight.

430
00:25:58,800 --> 00:26:02,679
Okay, so far I have found two T -shirts,
a bra and my Phat jeans.

431
00:26:03,920 --> 00:26:06,559
-What else do you have of mine?
-Nothing, I swear.

432
00:26:06,720 --> 00:26:10,554
-So you won't mind if I kept looking.
-You can look all night if you want.

433
00:26:11,840 --> 00:26:13,273
I won't be long.

434
00:26:17,840 --> 00:26:19,637
Breakups, huh?

435
00:26:19,800 --> 00:26:22,189
Get ready. You're next.

436
00:26:23,240 --> 00:26:25,834
-No, I'm not her--
-I'm sure you're not.

437
00:26:26,000 --> 00:26:27,274
My motorcycle boots.

438
00:26:27,440 --> 00:26:29,715
-Those are mine.
-How can you say these are yours?

439
00:26:29,880 --> 00:26:33,236
-Because I bought them.
-Okay, see, that is your problem.

440
00:26:33,400 --> 00:26:35,550
Okay. Here we go.

441
00:26:35,960 --> 00:26:39,236
-I'm gonna go to the bathroom.
-Tell me what my problem is.

442
00:26:39,400 --> 00:26:41,834
-I can't wait to hear.
-I don't know where to begin.

443
00:26:42,000 --> 00:26:44,594
You know what? Keep my boots.
Keep my records. It's fine.

444
00:26:44,760 --> 00:26:47,638
-It's not fine.
-What are you talking about?

445
00:26:47,800 --> 00:26:49,870
You can't just come here,
take all your stuff.

446
00:26:50,040 --> 00:26:52,315
Actually, I can.

447
00:26:56,240 --> 00:26:58,196
What do you want from me?

448
00:26:59,880 --> 00:27:01,393
I want you to stay.

449
00:27:08,280 --> 00:27:11,078
I want to talk about
what's going on here.

450
00:27:14,560 --> 00:27:16,312
Why don't you take Alex's jeep home.

451
00:27:16,480 --> 00:27:18,471
I'll bring her back later.

452
00:27:18,720 --> 00:27:19,994
I can't.

453
00:27:20,160 --> 00:27:22,435
-Why?
-You think I'd leave my girlfriend alone...

454
00:27:22,600 --> 00:27:25,558
-...with you overnight?
-I thought she wasn't your girlfriend.

455
00:27:25,720 --> 00:27:27,711
Yeah, well, think again.

456
00:27:33,240 --> 00:27:34,593
Let's go.

457
00:27:38,280 --> 00:27:39,793
Okay, that was awesome.

458
00:27:39,960 --> 00:27:41,518
Really? You think she bought it?

459
00:27:41,680 --> 00:27:43,511
She thought we
were sleeping together...

460
00:27:43,680 --> 00:27:45,989
-...when you met at the club last week.
-She did?

461
00:27:46,160 --> 00:27:48,196
-I defended your honor.
-I appreciate that.

462
00:27:48,400 --> 00:27:50,436
Are you kidding?
I owe you so much now.

463
00:27:50,640 --> 00:27:52,358
I got my Phat jeans, I got my CDs...

464
00:27:52,520 --> 00:27:55,956
...and who cares if I didn't get--
My heart.

465
00:27:56,120 --> 00:27:58,395
-How did you...?
-I'm sneaky like that.

466
00:28:00,560 --> 00:28:02,915
