467
00:28:11,200 --> 00:28:12,519
No.

468
00:28:13,160 --> 00:28:14,434
This one's yours.

469
00:28:29,040 --> 00:28:31,998
-How's it look?
-Good.

470
00:28:35,240 --> 00:28:39,870
-I guess we gotta get you home, huh?
-No. I have a better idea.

471
00:28:44,200 --> 00:28:46,714
-What do you think?
-I think you're the missing link...

472
00:28:46,880 --> 00:28:50,509
...between Jack Kirby and,
I don't know, Eric Wight.

473
00:28:50,680 --> 00:28:53,797
-Hey, thanks, man.
-Zach.

474
00:28:55,400 --> 00:28:58,278
I'm pulling the plug. You were supposed
to get me an hour ago.

475
00:28:58,440 --> 00:29:00,590
I know. I'm sorry.
Seth and I were working--

476
00:29:00,760 --> 00:29:04,116
I don't want hear it. What are
you guys, like, Kavalier and Gay?

477
00:29:04,280 --> 00:29:05,838
-That's funny.
-I know.

478
00:29:06,280 --> 00:29:08,874
I'm sorry. Listen, Seth, I'll call you.
We're leaving.

479
00:29:09,040 --> 00:29:11,031
Wait, wait, wait, whoa, whoa.
No, we're not.

480
00:29:11,200 --> 00:29:13,270
Is that supposed to be Marissa?

481
00:29:13,560 --> 00:29:15,551
Cohen, did you do these?

482
00:29:16,520 --> 00:29:19,114
Is that Ryan? Captain Oats.

483
00:29:20,200 --> 00:29:21,758
Is that you?

484
00:29:23,040 --> 00:29:24,393
Well....

485
00:29:27,280 --> 00:29:28,872
