486
00:29:29,400 --> 00:29:32,517
Not finished yet.
Just wanted to get the attitude right.

487
00:29:33,160 --> 00:29:35,116
There's a lot of attitude.

488
00:29:35,280 --> 00:29:38,750
-We made good progress today.
-It's definitely keeping my mind off girls.

489
00:29:38,920 --> 00:29:42,117
Keep talking comics, I don't think
girls will be an issue ever again.

490
00:29:42,280 --> 00:29:44,191
She's so supportive.
That's why I like her.

491
00:29:44,360 --> 00:29:46,749
Shoot. I left my purse upstairs.
I'll be right back.

492
00:29:46,920 --> 00:29:49,718
-We're gonna miss the movie.
-Whose fault is that?

493
00:29:57,200 --> 00:30:01,273
Sorry, Captain Oats.
Hope you don't pull up lame.

494
00:30:19,560 --> 00:30:21,790
Come on, Sum. We're gonna be late.

495
00:30:21,960 --> 00:30:23,598
What are you doing up there?

496
00:30:27,440 --> 00:30:28,919
Thank you.

497
00:30:34,440 --> 00:30:36,237
So, thank you...

498
00:30:36,520 --> 00:30:39,671
...so much for calling this afternoon
and suggesting dinner.

499
00:30:39,840 --> 00:30:41,558
-lt was--
-Long overdue.

500
00:30:41,720 --> 00:30:45,793
I meant to call you after the holidays,
but work has been all-consuming.

501
00:30:46,400 --> 00:30:48,436
Yeah, I'm sure. I mean...

502
00:30:49,000 --> 00:30:50,752
...I can imagine.

503
00:30:55,760 --> 00:30:59,196
So, what about you, Lindsay?
How is school?

504
00:30:59,600 --> 00:31:02,990
-What are you studying?
-Hey, sorry I'm late. Traffic.

505
00:31:03,360 --> 00:31:04,952
That's okay. We just got menus.

506
00:31:05,120 --> 00:31:08,829
My apologies. If I'd have known we'd be
three, I'd have asked for another one.

507
00:31:09,000 --> 00:31:11,639
Sorry. It's my fault.
I should've said something earlier.

508
00:31:11,800 --> 00:31:13,597
I should have assumed
Ryan would want...

509
00:31:13,760 --> 00:31:17,230
-...to make himself part of this.
-He didn't. I asked him to come.

510
00:31:17,440 --> 00:31:19,351
-Look, I can leave if you want.
-Yes, Ryan.

511
00:31:19,520 --> 00:31:22,478
You scammed your way into one
of my daughter's lives. Why stop?

512
00:31:22,640 --> 00:31:25,029
-This isn't about me.
-lsn't it? You set this up.

513
00:31:25,360 --> 00:31:28,238
-You came to my office and to dinner.
-You went to his office?

514
00:31:28,400 --> 00:31:29,674
I was trying to help.

515
00:31:29,840 --> 00:31:31,512
He said you wanted a relationship.

516
00:31:31,680 --> 00:31:35,229
If that were true, he wouldn't be here.
So, what do the two of you really want?

517
00:31:35,720 --> 00:31:37,073
Money?

518
00:31:37,480 --> 00:31:39,311
-What?
-A new car?

519
00:31:39,480 --> 00:31:42,233
An lvy League education?
Have your accomplice here...

520
00:31:42,400 --> 00:31:45,915
...drop by my office with a list
of demands. That should cover it.

521
00:31:46,080 --> 00:31:47,479
Good night.

522
00:31:49,760 --> 00:31:51,512
Hey, Mark. Sandy Cohen again.

523
00:31:51,680 --> 00:31:54,399
I know this is my fifth message today,
but I'm still up.

524
00:31:54,560 --> 00:31:58,394
So if you get this,
please call back. Thanks.

525
00:31:59,400 --> 00:32:03,109
-You gonna stay up all night?
-Well, I'm not tired, that's for sure.

526
00:32:03,280 --> 00:32:05,032
No word from your lawyer friend?

527
00:32:05,200 --> 00:32:09,432
No. No.
And no confirmation she's dead.

528
00:32:09,600 --> 00:32:12,910
What if she's not?
What if your suspicions are right?

529
00:32:13,680 --> 00:32:17,070
One way or another, she's gone.
What will it take for you to let her go?

530
00:32:17,240 --> 00:32:20,118
-What are you talking about?
-Rebecca Bloom.

531
00:32:20,440 --> 00:32:22,715
The smart, political, Jewish woman...

532
00:32:22,880 --> 00:32:26,714
...that you were supposed to marry
before you ended up with me.

533
00:32:27,400 --> 00:32:29,311
You're still in love with her.

534
00:32:35,120 --> 00:32:37,998
-That is not true.
-Then come to bed.

535
00:32:49,560 --> 00:32:51,915
Hello? Mark. Hey.

536
00:32:52,080 --> 00:32:55,834
I'm sorry to be harassing you,
but, you know, time is of the....

537
00:33:01,600 --> 00:33:03,158
Okay.

538
00:33:06,440 --> 00:33:08,192
Well, thanks for calling back.

539
00:33:08,480 --> 00:33:10,118
All right, take care.

540
00:33:17,840 --> 00:33:19,114
She's dead.

541
00:33:45,640 --> 00:33:48,313
-What are you gonna do?
-I gotta call the professor...

542
00:33:48,480 --> 00:33:51,119
...but l-- I can't tell him this
on the phone.

543
00:33:51,760 --> 00:33:53,591
I'm sorry.

544
00:33:56,040 --> 00:33:58,270
It was a long time ago.

545
00:33:58,920 --> 00:34:00,956
Maybe I need to let go of her too.

546
00:34:02,160 --> 00:34:03,752
I'm gonna go.

547
00:34:03,920 --> 00:34:05,512
I won't be long.

548
00:34:25,920 --> 00:34:29,117
Princess Sparkle,
you are not going to believe this.

549
00:35:07,960 --> 00:35:10,269
-I'm sorry.
-Why are you sorry?

550
00:35:10,440 --> 00:35:13,113
I made you come to dinner.
I know how much you hate him.

551
00:35:13,280 --> 00:35:15,669
-I don't hate him.
-Yeah.

552
00:35:15,840 --> 00:35:17,239
Well, he hates you.

553
00:35:18,880 --> 00:35:20,711
So for you to have gone to his office...

554
00:35:20,880 --> 00:35:23,314
-...for me was--
-A mistake.

555
00:35:25,880 --> 00:35:28,110
I really didn't want anything from him.

556
00:35:29,000 --> 00:35:32,390
I just wanted to ask him
some questions, you know?

557
00:35:33,200 --> 00:35:35,156
Stupid stuff.

558
00:35:37,120 --> 00:35:39,350
Maybe I don't need a dad.

559
00:35:40,760 --> 00:35:42,273
You know...

560
00:35:42,760 --> 00:35:45,354
...I've gone all this time without one.

561
00:35:45,640 --> 00:35:47,631
I turned out okay.

562
00:35:49,360 --> 00:35:50,998
Right?

563
00:35:57,800 --> 00:35:59,233
-Maybe I could talk to him.
-No.

564
00:35:59,400 --> 00:36:01,516
-Or ask Kirsten to talk to him.
-No.

565
00:36:01,680 --> 00:36:03,398
You've done enough.

566
00:36:03,720 --> 00:36:05,631
More than enough, and....

567
00:36:06,400 --> 00:36:08,311
You said it yourself.
He's not a good guy.

568
00:36:08,480 --> 00:36:10,118
Yeah, but he's your dad.

569
00:36:10,280 --> 00:36:12,111
-Are you sure I can't--?
-I'm sure.

570
00:36:12,720 --> 00:36:14,392
But thanks.

571
00:36:37,720 --> 00:36:39,836
Let me just change my shirt,
then we can go.

572
00:36:40,000 --> 00:36:44,357
-Your shirt is fine. I'm telling you.
-Then why is it sticking to me?

573
00:36:44,800 --> 00:36:47,360
-Am I bleeding?
-Let me see.

574
00:36:49,840 --> 00:36:53,469
Wow. No, you're not bleeding.
See for yourself.

575
00:36:53,640 --> 00:36:55,596
Oh, my god. That is so hot.

576
00:36:55,760 --> 00:36:57,318
Oh, my God.

577
00:36:57,480 --> 00:36:58,799
What have you done?

578
00:36:58,960 --> 00:37:01,110
Nothing. Get out of here, Caleb.

579
00:37:01,280 --> 00:37:03,077
This is my house. My home.

580
00:37:03,240 --> 00:37:05,231
Fine. You know what, then?
We'll leave.

581
00:37:07,000 --> 00:37:10,629
-You're not going anywhere.
-Oh, really? Are you gonna stop me?

582
00:37:12,520 --> 00:37:14,988
Yeah, that's what I thought.
Come on, Alex.

583
00:37:15,400 --> 00:37:16,674
Nice house.

584
00:37:21,600 --> 00:37:23,192
Come in.

585
00:37:28,520 --> 00:37:30,988
Hey. What are you doing here?

586
00:37:31,160 --> 00:37:35,870
I-- I came to return something
that I stole.

587
00:37:41,080 --> 00:37:43,310
Oh, you found it.

588
00:37:45,040 --> 00:37:46,553
Great.

589
00:37:46,920 --> 00:37:49,388
Okay, here's the thing.
I know it's totally creepy.

590
00:37:49,560 --> 00:37:51,596
Okay? I know that.
It was a very long summer.

591
00:37:51,880 --> 00:37:54,110
I'm sorry. I will destroy
all of them right now.

592
00:37:54,280 --> 00:37:57,352
-I just need to find my X-Acto knife.
-No, Cohen. Don't.

593
00:37:58,600 --> 00:38:00,318
-I think they're really good.
-Yeah?

594
00:38:00,480 --> 00:38:02,710
Yeah. I mean, well...

595
00:38:02,880 --> 00:38:06,429
...the boobs are a little big, but....
Well, I mean, aren't they?

596
00:38:06,800 --> 00:38:09,155
-We can redo the boobs.
-And, you know...

597
00:38:09,560 --> 00:38:11,471
...I'm not so sure
about the mask either.

598
00:38:21,880 --> 00:38:25,668
-Now, that's what I'm talking about.
-Yeah? So then you don't mind?

599
00:38:25,840 --> 00:38:29,355
No. Well, not as long
as I have boob approval.

600
00:38:29,600 --> 00:38:31,192
Okay.

601
00:38:32,360 --> 00:38:34,112
Do you mind if I have one of these?

602
00:38:34,960 --> 00:38:37,838
Yeah, sure. You can actually
have them all if you want.

603
00:38:38,200 --> 00:38:40,998
-Yeah?
-Although, maybe it's not a good idea...

604
00:38:41,160 --> 00:38:43,833
...to tell Zach about them all.

605
00:38:44,000 --> 00:38:46,594
-Or any of them.
-I was thinking the same thing.

606
00:38:46,760 --> 00:38:48,671
Just because it may
upset the partnership.

607
00:38:48,840 --> 00:38:51,912
-Yeah, and it could be bad for business.
-Exactly.

608
00:38:56,680 --> 00:38:58,432
Okay. I'll let you get back to work...

609
00:38:58,600 --> 00:39:02,070
...because I expect my own action figure
by Chrismukkah.

610
00:39:02,240 --> 00:39:05,835
-Wow. Okay. Well, I'll see what I can do.
-Okay.

611
00:39:06,040 --> 00:39:08,156
-Thanks, Cohen.
-Yeah.

612
00:39:36,200 --> 00:39:38,111
Hey, professor.

613
00:39:38,520 --> 00:39:43,196
Well, any chance
you could meet me tonight? Yeah.

614
00:39:43,440 --> 00:39:45,317
How about my office?

615
00:39:46,200 --> 00:39:47,713
I'll see you then.

616
00:39:56,120 --> 00:39:57,872
Hey, how was dinner?

617
00:39:58,040 --> 00:40:01,237
I wouldn't know.
Caleb took off before we could order.

618
00:40:01,480 --> 00:40:03,835
-Because you punched him in the face?
-No.

619
00:40:04,480 --> 00:40:07,278
But you wanted to.
I could tell you wanted to.

620
00:40:07,440 --> 00:40:09,795
That's good. Hey, listen,
he deserved it, I'm sure.

621
00:40:09,960 --> 00:40:11,632
I love the guy, but come on.

622
00:40:11,800 --> 00:40:14,394
-He's Lex Luthor.
-It's my fault. I keep trying to help.

623
00:40:14,560 --> 00:40:17,757
-I keep making everything worse.
-Well, Ryan, that's what heroes do.

624
00:40:17,920 --> 00:40:21,390
Okay, what else are you gonna do with
fists of fury? Homework? The dishes?

625
00:40:21,560 --> 00:40:24,791
-How'd it go with Zach?
-Great, until Summer came over...

626
00:40:24,960 --> 00:40:26,234
...and stole my sketchbook.

627
00:40:26,560 --> 00:40:29,552
-What? What'd she do?
-I thought she'd get a restraining order...

628
00:40:29,720 --> 00:40:32,359
...but it turns out she'll just get
her own action figure.

629
00:40:33,000 --> 00:40:35,036
-So she liked it?
-Yeah.

630
00:40:35,200 --> 00:40:37,794
Summer and I may be
stepping forward in our relationship.

631
00:40:37,960 --> 00:40:40,235
Knowing us, Lindsay and l
will take a step back.

632
00:40:40,400 --> 00:40:44,109
-Hey, so between the two of us....
-We're right back where we started.

633
00:40:44,280 --> 00:40:47,590
Well, at least
we haven't lost any ground.

634
00:40:48,240 --> 00:40:49,912
Except you won me. Here we go.

635
00:40:59,360 --> 00:41:02,272
Well, l....
I see you've got your hands full.

636
00:41:03,520 --> 00:41:05,317
I'm sorry to call you here so late.

637
00:41:05,480 --> 00:41:09,234
No, no, no. Actually, Sanford,
I was gonna call you.

638
00:41:09,880 --> 00:41:12,189
I have something to show you.

639
00:41:12,480 --> 00:41:13,993
What is it?

640
00:41:18,360 --> 00:41:20,032
Sandy Cohen.

641
00:41:22,840 --> 00:41:24,478
Rebecca.

